In [[Māori mythology|Māori tradition]], '''''Taikōria''''' was one of the great [[Māori migration canoes|ocean-going, voyaging canoes]] that was used in the migrations that settled [[New Zealand]]. Captained by [[Ruatāmore]], the ''Taikōria'' landed with the ''[[Kahutara]]'' and the ''[[Ōkoki]]'' at [[Ngāmotu]] near [[New Plymouth]].<ref>http://www.teara.govt.nz/NewZealanders/MaoriNewZealanders/CanoeTraditions/7/en Te Ara: Encyclopedia of New Zealand</ref>

